<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-18T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A Neutrality Patrol/68:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-18T13:00:00-06:00">January
                                    18, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3. Department’s instruction No. 357, December 12, 1939. Memorandum just
                            received from the Foreign Office states that the Guatemalan Government
                            will be pleased to conclude arrangements envisaged in the above
                            mentioned instruction. Will see the Foreign Minister immediately to
                            arrange exchange of memoranda in accordance with the Department’s
                            instruction.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>